AXIOS

Axios is a promise-based HTTP client for JavaScript used to send HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.) from the frontend or backend to APIs. It automatically handles JSON data, supports request/response interceptors, custom headers, timeouts, and better error handling than the native Fetch API.

Real example in your project

Jab user "Continue with Google" click karega:

Firebase Google login complete karega.
Frontend ko Google/Firebase token milega.
Axios us token ko Gateway/Auth Service ko bhejega.
Backend token verify karega, MongoDB me user create/login karega, aur JWT return karega.
Axios response receive karke user ko logged-in state me le aayega.

REDUX
Iska purpose hai user ki information ko poori application me globally store karna, taaki har component ko baar-baar API call na karni pade.
Har jagah office jaake ID banwane ki zarurat nahi padti.
Pocket (Redux Store) se ID nikal kar dikha dete ho.
Redux ka kaam bhi exactly yehi hai: ek baar user data store karo, phir poori app me use karo.

AGENT 
User frontend se prompt bhejega (e.g., "Make me a PPT on Docker").
Request API Gateway par aayegi.
Gateway request ko Agent Service ke paas forward karega.
Agent Service me LangGraph start hoga.
LangGraph ka Router Agent sabse pehle user ka prompt analyze karega.
Router decide karega ki kis specialized agent ko request bhejni hai.
Selected agent apna kaam complete karega.
Final response Agent Service → Gateway → Frontend return ho jayega.

FLOW 
START
   │
   ▼
Router Agent
   │
   ├────────► Chat Agent
   │
   ├────────► Web Search Agent
   │
   ├────────► Coding Agent
   │
   ├────────► PDF Agent
   │
   ├────────► PPT Agent
   │
   └────────► Image Agent
            │
            ▼
        Final Response
            │
            ▼
            END
API Gateway receives the user's request and forwards it to the Agent Service.
Inside the Agent Service, a LangGraph Router Agent acts as the brain of the system. It analyzes the user's prompt, determines the user's intent, and routes the request to the most suitable specialized agent. The Chat Agent handles general conversations using an LLM, the Web Search Agent retrieves real-time information from the internet, the Coding Agent generates and debugs code while providing previews, the PDF Agent creates PDF documents, the PPT Agent generates presentations, and the Image Agent creates AI-generated images. After the selected agent completes its task, the response is returned through the Agent Service and API Gateway back to the frontend. This modular architecture makes the platform scalable, allowing new agents to be added without changing the overall workflow.

